# PUSH — local environment template
#
# Copy this file to `.env` in this same folder (or just edit the `.env` that's
# already sitting here) and fill in real values. `.env` is gitignored — see the
# root .gitignore (`.env` / `.env.*` patterns) — nothing here ever reaches the
# public repo. This file (`.env.example`) has no real values and is safe to commit.
#
# These keys are needed in up to THREE places, not just here. This file is a
# single staging spot to fill them in once; where each one also needs to be
# copied to is noted per line.

# --- Telegram bot ---
# Create via @BotFather on Telegram (`/newbot`). Recommend a dedicated bot for
# PUSH rather than reusing an existing one (matches the one-bot-per-system
# pattern already used elsewhere: UpWork Engine, ETHAN, Harley each have their own).
# Also needed as: GitHub repo secret (push-poll.yml, push-dispatch.yml) AND
# an n8n credential (telegramApi type) if using the n8n front door.
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=

# Your personal numeric chat ID — the bot only ever acts on messages from this
# ID. Get it by messaging @userinfobot, or: send your new bot one message,
# then read the numeric chat.id off the first inbound webhook/update payload.
# Also needed as: GitHub repo secret, and as the allow-list value inside the
# n8n workflow's `if` node.
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=

# --- Anthropic (either one, not both required) ---
# The headless cold-start path (push-dispatch.yml) needs one of these two.
# Preferred: CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN — draws against a Pro/Max subscription
# instead of metered API billing. Generate it by running `claude setup-token`
# in YOUR OWN terminal (it opens a browser for OAuth login — cannot be run
# from inside a Claude Code session on your behalf). Valid for 1 year. Paste
# the result here, then it becomes the GitHub repo secret.
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=
# Fallback: metered API billing instead of subscription usage. Get one at
# https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys. Only needed if you're not
# using CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- GitHub (for n8n's use, NOT a GitHub Actions secret) ---
# NOT the same thing as GitHub Actions' own automatic GITHUB_TOKEN, and can't
# be set as a repo secret under that name — GitHub reserves it. This is a
# separate PAT, used only by n8n's HTTP Request node (or a manual curl test)
# to call the workflow_dispatch API from OUTSIDE the repo. Needs `repo` +
# `workflow` scope on dsvxmedia/Weapon-X.
# An existing n8n credential called "UpWork Engine GitHub Token" may already
# have the right scope — check that before minting a new one.
GH_WORKFLOW_DISPATCH_TOKEN=

# --- n8n (only if using the n8n front door instead of the GitHub cron poller) ---
# Base URL of your n8n instance. Already confirmed live: core.theclearstate.io
N8N_HOST=https://core.theclearstate.io
# API key for n8n's REST API (used to create/update the PUSH workflow
# programmatically rather than importing the JSON by hand). Same key already
# in use by n8n_self healer's own .env, if you'd rather point here at that.
N8N_API_KEY=
